Linux/Unix Environmentvariable has to set in **~/.bashrc**
- Open it with nano editor from WSL (if you have windows os)
- Go to the end of the file and add the command below:

JAVA_HOME="/mnt/c/PATH TO JDK/jdk-11.0.16.1"
PYTHON_HOME="/mnt/c/YOUR USERNAME/PATH TO PYTHON/Python310/"
SPARK_HOME="/mnt/c/YOUR USERNAME/PATH TO/spark-3.3.1-bin-hadoop3"
M2_HOME='/opt/apache-maven-3.9.0'
FLINK_HOME='/mnt/c/PATH TO FLINK/flink-1.18.0'

DRUID_JAVA_HOME='/usr/bin/perl'

PATH="$PATH:$JAVA_HOME/bin:$PYTHON_HOME:$SPARK_HOME/bin:$M2_HOME/bin:$FLINK_HOME/bin"
export PATH
